.TH INTERGEN 1 "2026-04-21" "intergen 0.1.0" "InterGenOS System Administration"
.SH NAME
intergen \- AI assistant for InterGenOS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B intergen
.I command
[\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B intergen
is the command-line interface to the InterGen AI assistant. It connects
to a running InterGen daemon over D-Bus when one is available and falls
back to an in-process direct session otherwise (useful for development
and first-run scenarios).
.PP
InterGen selects an LLM and quantisation appropriate to the local
hardware by detecting the system's CPU, RAM, and GPU at
.B intergen setup
time. The recommended model + quantisation and the hardware tier are
shown by
.BR "intergen tier" .
.PP
InterGen runs as a per-user systemd user service
.RB ( intergen.service )
with D-Bus activation on the session bus. The daemon starts
automatically when the first tool call arrives; it can also be started
explicitly with
.BR "intergen daemon" .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR ask " \fIMESSAGE\fR"
Ask InterGen a question or issue a natural-language instruction.
Returns the response on stdout. If no daemon is running a direct
session is started for the duration of the call.
.TP
.B status
Show daemon status: whether it is running, version, hardware tier,
number of requests handled, last error, and which internal components
are ready.
.TP
.B tier
Show hardware-tier detection results: tier level, RAM, GPU vendor and
model, recommended model and quantisation, and estimated model size on
disk.
.TP
.B tools
List the tools InterGen can invoke on the user's behalf, together with
their safety tier. Tools are scoped by the MCP permission configuration
in
.IR /etc/intergen/mcp.yml
and
.IR /etc/intergen/mcp.d/ .
.TP
.B test
Run the in-tree self-test (hardware detection + tool subsystem) and
exit with status 0 on success or 1 on failure. Primarily useful after
a configuration change or an upgrade.
.TP
.BR setup " [\fB\-\-yes\fR]"
Download and verify the recommended LLM model for the detected tier and
the embedding model. With
.B \-\-yes
runs non-interactively. Models are stored under
.IR /var/lib/intergen/models/ .
.TP
.B daemon
Start the InterGen daemon in the foreground. Normally run by the
systemd user service, not directly.
.TP
.BR help ", " \-\-help ", " \-h
Print usage.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/intergen/config.yml
System-wide configuration: LLM endpoint, sampling parameters, logging,
memory DB path, security policy location.
.TP
.I ~/.config/intergen/config.yml
Per-user overrides applied on top of the system-wide configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/intergen/mcp.yml
Top-level MCP configuration: which tools are enabled, their safety
tier, and their default invocation policy.
.TP
.I /etc/intergen/mcp.d/
Drop-in directory for MCP permission overrides. Files are applied
lexicographically.
.TP
.I /var/lib/intergen/models/
Local LLM and embedding models. Populated by
.BR "intergen setup" .
.TP
.I /var/lib/intergen/data/memory.db
InterGen's persistent memory/context database.
.TP
.I /var/log/intergen/intergen.log
Main log. See
.I /var/log/intergen/events.jsonl
for the structured event log and
.I /var/log/intergen/mcp-audit.log
for the MCP tool-call audit trail.
.SH EXAMPLES
Ask a question:
.PP
.RS
.B intergen ask "What desktop packages are installed?"
.RE
.PP
Check that the daemon is running and healthy:
.PP
.RS
.B intergen status
.RE
.PP
Confirm the hardware tier InterGen detected:
.PP
.RS
.B intergen tier
.RE
.PP
Download the recommended model non-interactively:
.PP
.RS
.B intergen setup \-\-yes
.RE
.PP
List callable tools and their safety tiers:
.PP
.RS
.B intergen tools
.RE
.SH SECURITY
InterGen treats every tool call as a privileged action. The default
escalation mode is
.BR ask ,
requiring user confirmation for any tool invocation that modifies
system state. Safety tiers and per-tool policies are configured in
.I /etc/intergen/mcp.yml
and
.IR /etc/intergen/mcp.d/ ;
a stored schema pin at
.I /var/lib/intergen/mcp-pins/
prevents silent tool-signature drift between upgrades.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pkm (1),
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR journalctl (1)
